body:
Migrated from: https://github.com/measurement-kit/measurement-kit/issues/1125

Diagnosis: I noticed that, commenting out the following code:

```Java
.on_entry(new org.openobservatory.measurement_kit.nettests.EntryCallback() {
    @Override
    public void callback(String entry) {
        setAnomaly(entry, currentTest);
    }
})
```

made the crash disappear. As such, I am inclined to think that the issue lies in the Java side (or perhaps is *implied* by the currently used design, but still the fix must be done here).
